						<summary>

						<p>Slab on the western side of the Mallikārjuna temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">16th-17th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged record mentions the setting up of the image of Nandi in front of Mallaiyadēva (the god) by a lady in the presence of several officers (named) and <hi rend="italic">mahājanas.</hi> The pontiff of Śringeri is mentioned here.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 16th-17th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
